Hi,
I am currently facing a problem with a route which lets users download files. The filename and the hash of the file are first queried from a database and then used in the `res.download` method to let the user download the file.

It is possible however, that under the same route, the file might change. That's because a file in my app has an id and the file can be changed afterwards (for example a new revision). The problem I am facing is, that Google Chrome will get an ERR_INVALID_RESPONSE error when the file behind the logic changes. It works however fine with Internet Explorer.

This is the route's code:
```
// download document
router.get('/dl/:id', function(req, res){
	
	// TODO: check permissions
	var id = req.param('id');
	var sql = req.sql;
	var hash;
	var filename;

	var ddq = new sql.Request();
	ddq.stream = true;
	ddq.input('documentID', sql.Int, id);
	ddq.execute('getDocumentDataForDownload');
	ddq.on('row', function(row){
		hash = row.document_hash;
		filename = row.document_real_name;
		console.log(hash);
		console.log(filename);
	});
	ddq.on('done', function(v){
		res.download('./fs/' + hash, filename, function(err){
			if(err){
				console.log(err);
			}
		});
	});
});
```

Express Version 4.11

Any ideas what could cause this problem?

